<dl id="n12004d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12004d">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12004d"> 4(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Louannec, Dolmen, S Yves&apos; bed</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A <mark>Louaennec</mark> (C&ocirc;tes-du-Nord), <mark>un dolmen servait de lit &agrave; saint Yves</mark> qui venait souvent s&apos;y reposer apr&egrave;s ses courses apostoliques. <br><font color="green">[In Louaennec (C&ocirc;tes-du-Nord) a dolmen served as a bed for Saint Yves who frequently came to rest on it after his apostolic roamings.]</font> <small> l'Abb&eacute; A. Millon, <a name="AMPB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#AMPB"><cite title="source">Pauvres Pierres! Les Megalithes Bretons devant la science</cite></a> (n.d) 9</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
